# TypeScript Domain and Event Conventions

## Shared library usage

- Keep domain definitions in shared libraries outside `api` and `client`.
- Import shared domain types and contracts instead of redefining them locally.
- If duplication appears across packages, extract to shared lib in the same PR.

## Domain vs contracts

- Domain types express business intent and invariants.
- Contract types express boundary payloads (HTTP, queue, integration).
- Map contract -> domain and domain -> contract explicitly in adapter layers.

## Event modeling

- Define event names as stable string literals in a central shared location.
- Keep event payloads minimal but complete for downstream consumers.
- Add `schemaVersion` when event shape changes are possible.
- Do not perform side effects in event constructors/factories.

## Testing expectations

- Add unit tests for aggregate invariants and value object validation.
- Add tests for event emission and idempotent handler behavior.
